1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.500 --> 00:00:03.480
US, US

3
00:00:04.100 --> 00:00:09.340
US, ALL OF US

4
00:00:12.970 --> 00:00:15.770
The end of the dream, the end of the sea

5
00:00:15.770 --> 00:00:17.750
We all have different places we want to go We all have different places we want to go WE ALL HAVE DIFFERENT PLACES WE WANT TO GO

6
00:00:15.790 --> 00:00:18.530
We all have different places we want to go

7
00:00:18.530 --> 00:00:21.310
But to start we've got to show what we're made of

8
00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:25.660
We'll be legends, we're gonna take the world by storm

9
00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:29.250
Sparks are flying, NO LIMITS! This is where it starts

10
00:00:29.250 --> 00:00:30.530
ONE PIECE!!

11
00:00:30.890 --> 00:00:33.510
VORONOI START VORONOI END ALL OF US, I've got a question for you ALL OF US, I've got a question for you

12
00:00:33.510 --> 00:00:37.100
Have you let the world and all its burdens bring your dreams down?

13
00:00:38.740 --> 00:00:45.300
Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much

14
00:00:45.410 --> 00:00:52.030
Still we try, ALL OF US have our own paths we cling to

15
00:00:52.030 --> 00:00:54.620
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you

16
00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:55.150
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

17
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:58.200
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

18
00:00:54.740 --> 00:00:58.050
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

19
00:00:59.890 --> 00:01:02.580
Random clues suddenly fit together

20
00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:06.510
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

21
00:01:06.510 --> 00:01:12.980
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

22
00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:18.680
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

23
00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:21.250
US, US

24
00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:26.360
US, ALL OF US

25
00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:35.330
<b>Future Island, Egghead</b>

26
00:01:37.540 --> 00:01:42.420
Now that I'm aboard this ship,
I guess it's my problem, too!

27
00:01:42.420 --> 00:01:45.750
My new captain is quite the handful!

28
00:01:47.170 --> 00:01:48.250
Luffy!

29
00:01:48.670 --> 00:01:51.510
I love it! I love your dream!

30
00:01:51.510 --> 00:01:52.590
Yeah?

31
00:01:52.590 --> 00:01:54.470
It's the best!

32
00:01:55.220 --> 00:01:56.140
Whoa-whoa!

33
00:01:56.140 --> 00:01:58.560
Yeah, that's just like you...

34
00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:03.190
But you gotta be the Pirate King
to make it happen!

35
00:02:03.190 --> 00:02:08.320
We're just one lode poneglyph away
from setting course for Laugh Tale!

36
00:02:08.320 --> 00:02:10.990
Don't make it sound so simple, Franky.

37
00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:16.530
That last lode poneglyph will be
the most difficult one to find.

38
00:02:19.290 --> 00:02:20.660
Because...

39
00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:23.290
unlike the others,

40
00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:28.670
no one has found it for a very long time...

41
00:02:29.050 --> 00:02:31.300
There are no leads whatsoever.

42
00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:42.810
<b>Marine Headquarters
New World</b>

43
00:02:45.060 --> 00:02:48.150
Signal from Flame Emperor Sabo
to the Kamabakka Queendom!

44
00:02:48.150 --> 00:02:48.900
Alright!

45
00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:50.650
Where is he?!

46
00:02:50.650 --> 00:02:52.400
Make sure you trace his position!

47
00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:54.860
No jamming from a white transponder snail!

48
00:02:54.860 --> 00:02:58.240
He's done nothing to prevent wiretapping?

49
00:02:58.240 --> 00:03:01.200
This must be an emergency call!
It won't last long!

50
00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:03.910
We finally got a lead on his whereabouts!

51
00:03:04.290 --> 00:03:06.040
Don't miss this chance!

52
00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:10.250
<b>Room of Authority
Pangaea Castle
The Holy Land, Mary Geoise</b>

53
00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:16.680
The trace was successful!

54
00:03:16.680 --> 00:03:17.800
Where is it from?!

55
00:03:18.800 --> 00:03:20.810
The Kingdom of Lulusia!

56
00:03:22.060 --> 00:03:23.640
Lulusia...

57
00:03:23.640 --> 00:03:24.890
My word...

58
00:03:24.890 --> 00:03:29.440
It's one of the countries where
the simultaneous Eight-Nation Revolution

59
00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:31.980
took place after the Reverie!

60
00:03:31.980 --> 00:03:34.820
It's an ideal hiding spot for Sabo!

61
00:03:35.450 --> 00:03:37.160
I see...

62
00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:39.120
What an unfortunate man...

63
00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:42.330
No...

64
00:03:44.120 --> 00:03:46.160
This is simply fate...

65
00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:51.590
<b>Kamabakka Queendom</b>

66
00:03:51.590 --> 00:03:53.710
Great! I got through!

67
00:03:56.220 --> 00:03:57.430
Sabo...

68
00:03:57.430 --> 00:03:58.800
Sabo!

69
00:03:58.800 --> 00:04:01.930
We haven't heard from you
in a while, so what gives?!

70
00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:06.140
I vass really voorried about you!

71
00:04:06.140 --> 00:04:07.770
I'm sorry, everyone.

72
00:04:07.770 --> 00:04:09.310
No!

73
00:04:09.310 --> 00:04:10.520
That's okay!

74
00:04:10.520 --> 00:04:12.020
We love you!

75
00:04:12.020 --> 00:04:14.780
That's enough celebrating.

76
00:04:14.780 --> 00:04:19.530
You didn't contact us just to
tell us you're alive, did you?

77
00:04:21.160 --> 00:04:22.370
No...

78
00:04:22.370 --> 00:04:26.250
I suppose you've all read
the news article by now.

79
