<b>REVOLUTIONARY ARMY CHIEF OF STAFF SABO

ASSASSINATES KING COBRA OF ALABASTA</b>

80
00:04:34.340 --> 00:04:35.800
Dragon!

81
00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:38.550
King Cobra's assassin...

82
00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:44.390
wasn't me!

83
00:04:47.060 --> 00:04:48.140
Yeah!

84
00:04:48.140 --> 00:04:50.310
I believed you!

85
00:04:50.310 --> 00:04:52.650
I did not need to hear it! I knew it!

86
00:04:53.020 --> 00:04:53.860
But...

87
00:04:56.360 --> 00:04:58.530
when I was at Mary Geoise...

88
00:04:59.110 --> 00:05:01.450
I saw something unthinkable!

89
00:05:01.450 --> 00:05:03.280
Something unthinkable?

90
00:05:10.080 --> 00:05:13.580
<b>Kingdom of Lulusia
Grand Line</b>

91
00:05:22.510 --> 00:05:23.510
Hey.

92
00:05:25.850 --> 00:05:26.850
Look.

93
00:05:31.440 --> 00:05:32.810
What is that?

94
00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:34.560
It's creepy...

95
00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:36.190
It's almost like...

96
00:05:36.190 --> 00:05:39.610
there's something massive up there...

97
00:05:41.450 --> 00:05:44.030
You cretins will all regret this!

98
00:05:44.030 --> 00:05:48.540
Once Marine Headquarters hears
about this, you'll all be impaled!

99
00:05:44.070 --> 00:05:48.410
<b>Princess Comane
Kingdom of Lulusia</b>
<b>King Seki
Kingdom of Lulusia</b>

100
00:05:48.540 --> 00:05:50.620
Dad, let me do it, too!

101
00:05:50.620 --> 00:05:53.500
You vermin, I'll make you pay for this!

102
00:05:53.500 --> 00:05:55.590
Your Maje– I mean, Seki, sir!

103
00:05:56.210 --> 00:06:01.970
If you had thought of your citizens
even a little bit, we wouldn't have revolted.

104
00:06:01.970 --> 00:06:03.300
If I had what?!

105
00:06:03.300 --> 00:06:06.970
Why should a king spare a thought
for his lowly citizens?!

106
00:06:07.510 --> 00:06:10.060
Know your place! How dare you!

107
00:06:10.060 --> 00:06:11.930
Please confess to your crimes!

108
00:06:11.930 --> 00:06:14.190
We don't want to take your lives...

109
00:06:15.270 --> 00:06:18.980
Just shut up and let me out of here!

110
00:06:34.670 --> 00:06:37.880
In Pangaea Castle where
the Reverie took place...

111
00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:40.340
on the Empty Throne...

112
00:06:40.340 --> 00:06:43.550
Communications, 
cut off your transponder snail.

113
00:06:43.550 --> 00:06:44.470
What?

114
00:06:44.930 --> 00:06:46.550
Did you not hear me?

115
00:06:47.510 --> 00:06:49.060
Y-Yes, sir!

116
00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:54.190
There's no king over the whole world,
so that throne should be empty...!

117
00:06:56.190 --> 00:06:57.650
Communications,

118
00:06:58.150 --> 00:06:59.610
listen carefully...

119
00:07:09.490 --> 00:07:13.200
You did not trace any calls...

120
00:07:14.960 --> 00:07:17.040
Dad, I'm scared.

121
00:07:21.420 --> 00:07:24.340
You did not wiretap anything...

122
00:07:27.340 --> 00:07:29.970
The Kingdom of Lulusia?

123
00:07:36.310 --> 00:07:38.400
Such a country...

124
00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:50.070
never even existed...

125
00:08:10.300 --> 00:08:11.760
What's happening?!

126
00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:37.580
Sabo?

127
00:08:37.580 --> 00:08:39.080
Sabo?!

128
00:08:46.880 --> 00:08:49.800
Seaquake off the southeast coast!
Prepare for a tsunami!

129
00:08:50.510 --> 00:08:51.510
I repeat!

130
00:08:51.510 --> 00:08:54.970
Seaquake off the southeast coast!
Prepare for a tsunami!

131
00:08:59.140 --> 00:09:04.320
<b>A Few Days Later</b>

132
00:09:10.820 --> 00:09:13.530
I'm gonna die! I'm dead!

133
00:09:21.250 --> 00:09:22.540
It's cold!

134
00:09:22.540 --> 00:09:24.130
I'm scared!

135
00:09:24.130 --> 00:09:25.710
We're done for!

136
00:09:25.710 --> 00:09:27.050
Help!

137
00:09:33.260 --> 00:09:34.890
– A sea king!
– A sea king!

138
00:09:43.520 --> 00:09:45.980
This is absurd!

139
00:09:50.690 --> 00:09:52.570
Aren't you cold?!

140
00:09:52.570 --> 00:09:54.780
It's all a matter of perception.

141
00:09:55.660 --> 00:09:57.410
It must be good to be moss, huh?

142
00:09:57.410 --> 00:09:59.080
You're too dull to feel cold.

143
00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:02.870
Want me to turn you into fish food?!

144
00:10:02.870 --> 00:10:04.080
Try it!

145
00:10:04.460 --> 00:10:07.340
Is this really the time?
Knock it off, you two!

146
00:10:07.340 --> 00:10:08.300
Jinbe!

147
00:10:08.670 --> 00:10:10.550
Watch out for ice floes!

148
00:10:10.550 --> 00:10:11.760
You got it!

149
00:10:24.230 --> 00:10:25.860
Furl the sails!

150
00:10:25.860 --> 00:10:27.570
The winds are too strong!

151
00:10:28.900 --> 00:10:30.070
All right!

152
00:10:36.160 --> 00:10:39.290
Strong Right!

153
00:10:47.750 --> 00:10:50.090
Move faster, Moss Head!

154
00:10:50.090 --> 00:10:52.760
Can't you just work quietly?

155
00:10:56.010 --> 00:10:58.510
Are we near the island yet, Nami?!

156
00:10:59.260 --> 00:11:01.470
I don't think it's that far away!

157
00:11:01.930 --> 00:11:06.020
I believe we've entered
the island's climate zone...

158
00:11:06.020 --> 00:11:08.980
I'm guessing it's a harsh winter island!

159
00:11:14.950 --> 00:11:18.070
Seems like they're having
a hard time, so I'm gonna go help!

160
00:11:18.070 --> 00:11:19.450
Oh my,

161
00:11:19.450 --> 00:11:21.290
you look dashing, Chopper.

162
00:11:23.330 --> 00:11:29.250
Otama bestowed upon me this woven hat,
thus these winter storms pose no threat!

163
00:11:29.250 --> 00:11:30.090
Right?!

164
00:11:34.670 --> 00:11:36.260
Hey, Nami!

165
00:11:36.260 --> 00:11:37.640
What's that?!

166
00:11:38.090 --> 00:11:40.180
What's what?

167
00:11:49.730 --> 00:11:50.940
What is that?!

168
00:11:50.940 --> 00:11:53.690
That's a big warm eddy!

169
00:11:53.690 --> 00:11:55.530
An eddy?! That?!

170
00:11:55.530 --> 00:11:57.820
What in the hell is that thing?!

171
00:11:57.820 --> 00:11:59.490
You've gotta be kidding!

172
00:11:59.490 --> 00:12:02.700
Why is it so far above the surface?!

173
00:12:02.700 --> 00:12:07.000
It's a mass of heated water that's been
pushed above the surface somehow.

174
00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:09.000
How hot would it have to be?!

175
00:12:11.460 --> 00:12:13.250
It's like an afro!

176
00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:15.460
Get us out of here, Jinbe!
We'll get pulled in!

177
00:12:16.090 --> 00:12:17.090
Leave it to me!

178
00:12:17.090 --> 00:12:18.090
Wait!

179
00:12:19.300 --> 00:12:21.390
Someone's there! Inside the water!

180
00:12:23.060 --> 00:12:25.520
What?! No way!

181
00:12:25.520 --> 00:12:26.520
A mermaid?!

182
00:12:29.940 --> 00:12:33.400
Somebody!

183
00:12:34.280 --> 00:12:35.900
There's no mistake!

184
00:12:35.900 --> 00:12:37.780
I hear a lady's scream!

185
00:12:37.780 --> 00:12:39.150
From inside the water?!

186
00:12:42.370 --> 00:12:44.450
Are you serious?!

187
00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:52.130
Even if someone is there, what can we do?!

188
00:12:53.460 --> 00:12:55.210
We can just cut it...

189
00:13:00.130 --> 00:13:02.890
If you so much as scratch the lady,

190
00:13:02.890 --> 00:13:04.760
I'll fillet you!

191
00:13:04.760 --> 00:13:06.100
Shut up!

192
00:13:17.650 --> 00:13:19.360
One-Sword Style:

193
00:13:26.830 --> 00:13:28.700
Bird Dance!

194
00:13:34.920 --> 00:13:37.130
– He cut it!
– He cut it!

195
00:13:40.670 --> 00:13:41.970
Hey, guys!

196
00:13:41.970 --> 00:13:43.680
What's all the fuss about?!

197
00:13:44.180 --> 00:13:45.220
Don't worry!

198
00:13:45.220 --> 00:13:48.140
Woven-Hat Chopperemon is here, so–

199
00:13:50.060 --> 00:13:51.310
The wind is so strong!

200
00:13:52.390 --> 00:13:54.940
Why did you even come out here, Chopper?!

201
00:13:55.900 --> 00:13:57.650
Help!

202
00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:00.530
Chopper!

203
00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:04.370
Luffy!

204
00:14:07.790 --> 00:14:09.500
Not you too!

205
00:14:09.870 --> 00:14:11.080
What are you doing?!

206
00:14:11.080 --> 00:14:12.460
That idiot!

207
00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:26.680
<b>Jewelry Bonney "the Glutton"
Worst Generation</b>
<b>Bounty:    320 Million</b>

208
00:14:27.140 --> 00:14:28.890
A kid popped outta the water!

209
00:14:29.560 --> 00:14:31.230
Who is that?

210
00:14:39.230 --> 00:14:40.150
Who are you?!

211
00:14:42.320 --> 00:14:43.650
Thank good–

212
00:14:44.320 --> 00:14:45.320
Wait, the monster!

213
00:14:46.570 --> 00:14:48.830
Oh, good! Seems like she's alive...

214
00:14:48.830 --> 00:14:49.790
But...

215
00:14:49.120 --> 00:14:50.870
Below you!

216
00:14:49.790 --> 00:14:52.790
Where do they think they're going?!

217
00:14:50.870 --> 00:14:52.790
It's there!

218
00:14:52.790 --> 00:14:56.250
That little kid's yelling something!

219
00:14:53.660 --> 00:14:56.250
It's still there!

220
00:14:56.750 --> 00:14:58.250
Below you!

221
00:14:58.250 --> 00:14:59.500
Look down!

222
00:15:00.250 --> 00:15:02.130
"Look down"...?

223
00:15:10.140 --> 00:15:11.970
What is it this time?!

224
00:15:11.970 --> 00:15:13.730
Go away!

225
00:15:13.730 --> 00:15:16.190
– Oh my gosh! Oh my gosh! Oh my gosh!
– What's going on?!

226
00:15:16.190 --> 00:15:18.770
– Help!
– Help!

227
00:15:20.150 --> 00:15:22.030
These waters aren't safe!

228
00:15:22.030 --> 00:15:23.070
Get us out of here!

229
00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:41.040
Is this it for us?!

230
00:15:42.170 --> 00:15:43.880
Jinbe! Hurry up!

231
00:15:44.300 --> 00:15:47.340
Jinbe! Get us out of here!

232
00:15:47.340 --> 00:15:49.850
Hold on!

233
00:15:49.850 --> 00:15:52.310
Hurry!

234
00:16:00.980 --> 00:16:02.610
What is that thing?!

235
00:16:02.610 --> 00:16:04.860
That's no ordinary shark!

236
00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:07.860
It's way too big, and it's made of metal?!

237
00:16:10.370 --> 00:16:11.740
Hold on tight!

238
00:16:11.740 --> 00:16:13.370
We're about to hit water!

239
00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:24.210
Damn! They fell into the sea!

240
00:16:24.210 --> 00:16:25.880
This is bad!

241
00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:27.170
Franky!

242
00:16:27.170 --> 00:16:28.800
Take the helm!

243
00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:32.470
Bring the ship around to us!

244
00:16:34.560 --> 00:16:36.770
Alright! You can count on me!

245
00:16:45.530 --> 00:16:47.150
I told him to count on me,

246
00:16:47.150 --> 00:16:50.110
but how do I find them
when the water's this rough?

247
00:16:50.110 --> 00:16:52.320
Guess I just gotta do it.

248
00:17:00.670 --> 00:17:02.420
Ship's Bottom:

249
00:17:07.460 --> 00:17:08.880
Rabbit...

250
00:17:11.220 --> 00:17:14.430
Screw!

251
00:17:14.300 --> 00:17:14.350
<b>SHIP'S BOTTOM:</b>
<b>RABBIT SCREW</b>

252
00:17:14.350 --> 00:17:14.390
<b>SHIP'S BOTTOM:</b>
<b>RABBIT SCREW</b>

253
00:17:14.390 --> 00:17:14.430
<b>SHIP'S BOTTOM:</b>
<b>RABBIT SCREW</b>

254
