291
00:17:22.480 --> 00:17:24.770
Time to mount a rescue!

292
00:17:38.370 --> 00:17:40.750
Luffy! Chopper!

293
00:17:40.750 --> 00:17:42.580
Where are you?!

294
00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:51.470
Franky! Get us out of here!

295
00:17:51.470 --> 00:17:53.930
Torpedoes!

296
00:18:00.640 --> 00:18:02.600
Robin! Nami!

297
00:18:03.440 --> 00:18:04.400
Oh, crap!

298
00:18:04.400 --> 00:18:07.770
We're gonna capsize!

299
00:18:24.580 --> 00:18:27.090
What was that explosion?

300
00:18:31.050 --> 00:18:33.180
Luffy! Chopper!

301
00:18:33.180 --> 00:18:35.590
I'm here! You'll be alright!

302
00:18:43.690 --> 00:18:46.560
Hey, you three! Stay with me!

303
00:18:46.560 --> 00:18:48.020
We're about to surface!

304
00:18:54.780 --> 00:18:56.530
The current is too strong!

305
00:18:56.530 --> 00:18:58.240
The rudder can't take it!

306
00:19:00.910 --> 00:19:02.950
Thank you, Jinbe...

307
00:19:02.950 --> 00:19:05.750
I'm glad that all of you are okay!

308
00:19:08.290 --> 00:19:11.420
The Sunny will be here soon!

309
00:19:27.310 --> 00:19:29.310
What's the matter, Jinbe?

310
00:19:30.570 --> 00:19:32.610
Hold on tight!

311
00:19:34.820 --> 00:19:37.240
We'll escape below the surface!

312
00:19:37.240 --> 00:19:40.280
Take a deep breath, guys!

313
00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:49.130
Let's go!

314
00:20:10.230 --> 00:20:11.270
Oh, no...

315
00:20:11.270 --> 00:20:12.860
The current is too strong!

316
00:20:12.860 --> 00:20:14.230
We can't surface!

317
00:20:14.940 --> 00:20:16.990
Somebody, help!

318
00:20:16.990 --> 00:20:20.240
Why am I underwater?! What's going on?!

319
00:20:20.700 --> 00:20:22.700
Hang in there, Robin!

320
00:20:23.330 --> 00:20:24.830
Nami!

321
00:21:18.300 --> 00:21:21.220
We're in trouble...
If we don't do something...

322
00:21:22.720 --> 00:21:24.510
we'll all die.

323
00:21:39.030 --> 00:21:41.740
<b>At a Nearby Island</b>
<b>Marine Branch G-14</b>

324
00:21:39.530 --> 00:21:41.740
All right, everyone!

325
00:21:41.740 --> 00:21:45.200
<b>Captain Tashigi
Marine Headquarters</b>

326
00:21:42.240 --> 00:21:44.240
It's time for your medicine!

327
00:21:45.700 --> 00:21:47.330
One cup each!

328
00:21:47.330 --> 00:21:48.410
You can do it!

329
00:21:50.540 --> 00:21:53.830
I'll drink it, but only because
you told me to, Tashigi!

330
00:21:54.960 --> 00:21:56.170
Thank you!

331
00:21:56.170 --> 00:21:59.380
Make sure you drink all of it!

332
00:21:58.710 --> 00:22:00.380
It tastes weird!

333
00:22:00.380 --> 00:22:02.130
I don't wanna, it tastes awful!

334
00:22:02.470 --> 00:22:04.260
But you should still try!

335
00:22:05.930 --> 00:22:08.180
Do I have to drink the whole thing?

336
00:22:08.180 --> 00:22:11.140
Yeah, to return to your original size.

337
00:22:11.140 --> 00:22:14.270
I wanna return faster, so I'll drink two!

338
00:22:14.650 --> 00:22:15.730
Tashigi!

339
00:22:16.360 --> 00:22:18.440
I think I'm a lot smaller now!

340
00:22:19.570 --> 00:22:21.400
I can hardly recognize you, Mocha!

341
00:22:21.780 --> 00:22:23.860
I can't wait to go home!

342
00:22:23.860 --> 00:22:26.780
Yeah, be patient just a little longer.

343
00:22:26.780 --> 00:22:27.870
Try to hang in there!

344
00:22:27.870 --> 00:22:29.450
Tashigi!

345
00:22:30.330 --> 00:22:31.750
Vice Admiral Doll!

346
00:22:32.120 --> 00:22:33.960
Can I steal you for a sec?

347
00:22:37.250 --> 00:22:41.460
<b>Vice Admiral Doll
Marine Branch G-14 Commander</b>

348
00:22:37.340 --> 00:22:41.460
Could you do something about
that Helmeppo brat?

349
00:22:41.970 --> 00:22:44.930
There's nothing I can do.

350
00:22:44.930 --> 00:22:47.390
His best friend's safety is in question.

351
00:22:47.760 --> 00:22:51.770
Captain Koby is an important
colleague to me, too...

352
00:22:51.770 --> 00:22:54.520
I'm begging you guys!

353
00:22:54.520 --> 00:22:57.770
We're comrades, aren't we? Please!

354
00:22:58.520 --> 00:23:04.700
<b>Commander Hibari
Marine Headquarters
(SWORD)</b>
<b>Lieutenant Commander Helmeppo
Marine Headquarters
(SWORD)</b>

355
00:22:58.650 --> 00:23:01.230
I'm beggin' you, too!

356
00:23:01.230 --> 00:23:04.700
Koby's always looked out for me!

357
00:23:04.700 --> 00:23:07.950
<b>Rear Admiral Prince Grus
Marine Headquarters
(SWORD)</b>

358
00:23:05.160 --> 00:23:07.950
Please come with us to Pirate Island!

359
00:23:07.950 --> 00:23:09.370
Prince!

360
00:23:12.040 --> 00:23:13.200
Please!

361
00:23:13.200 --> 00:23:15.750
We can't do it on our own!

362
00:23:16.630 --> 00:23:18.340
Prince!

363
00:23:18.340 --> 00:23:20.170
I'm begging you!

364
00:23:20.710 --> 00:23:21.840
Please!

365
00:23:21.840 --> 00:23:24.880
I won't move an inch until you join us!

366
00:23:25.510 --> 00:23:29.350
Koby's been taken to Pirate Island...

367
00:23:29.350 --> 00:23:31.640
That's Emperor Blackbeard's home turf!

368
00:23:34.770 --> 00:23:36.270
You understand, right?!

369
00:23:37.020 --> 00:23:40.270
If you poke that island even a little...

370
00:23:40.570 --> 00:23:44.490
bloodthirsty pirates will swarm you like bees!

371
00:23:47.610 --> 00:23:50.330
That's why it's called Beehive!

372
00:23:51.080 --> 00:23:53.160
Egghead isn't far from here!

373
00:23:55.120 --> 00:23:57.620
We could deploy the seraphim!

374
00:23:57.620 --> 00:23:59.380
The seraphim?!

375
00:23:59.380 --> 00:24:00.840
Are you out of your mind?!

376
00:24:01.630 --> 00:24:03.460
You need to calm down!

377
00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:09.680
We can't even contact Drake right now...

378
00:24:10.300 --> 00:24:12.100
There's nothing we can do!

379
00:24:16.730 --> 00:24:18.230
You must understand.

380
00:24:20.560 --> 00:24:23.020
Koby!

381
00:24:27.530 --> 00:24:29.280
What?!

382
00:24:28.780 --> 00:24:31.490
<b>Luffy's Group</b>

383
00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:31.490
Don't you know who I am?!

384
00:24:31.490 --> 00:24:33.330
Nope. I don't know.

385
00:24:33.740 --> 00:24:38.540
We were both labeled as part
of the Worst Generation!

386
00:24:38.540 --> 00:24:41.670
Oh, you're one of the worst, too?

387
00:24:42.540 --> 00:24:44.130
This guy's an idiot!

388
00:24:46.800 --> 00:24:50.300
I was there at Sabaody too, two years ago!

389
00:24:51.680 --> 00:24:53.680
I'm Bonney!

390
00:24:53.680 --> 00:24:55.600
Remember, we're enemies!

391
00:24:56.600 --> 00:24:59.060
Then again, you did save me...

392
00:25:00.190 --> 00:25:01.480
So thanks for that.

393
00:25:02.110 --> 00:25:04.230
Don't mention it, Bogey!

394
00:25:04.650 --> 00:25:05.980
It's Bonney!

395
00:25:06.820 --> 00:25:08.070
What the...

396
00:25:11.110 --> 00:25:12.700
That's cold!

397
00:25:13.620 --> 00:25:16.080
I'm invincible with my woven hat!

398
00:25:17.120 --> 00:25:19.160
I won't lose either, Chopper!

399
00:25:20.670 --> 00:25:22.250
This guy's an Emperor...?

400
00:25:22.710 --> 00:25:25.090
And Jinbe, Knight of the Sea,
really did join his crew...

401
00:25:25.920 --> 00:25:28.550
Oh yeah, what's up with that wanted poster?

402
00:25:28.550 --> 00:25:31.510
Your hair was all white.

403
00:25:31.510 --> 00:25:33.470
It was all over the news.

404
00:25:33.470 --> 00:25:35.390
Oh, that's...

405
00:25:37.890 --> 00:25:40.270
just how I look when I'm free!

406
00:25:40.270 --> 00:25:42.190
What the hell?

407
00:25:42.190 --> 00:25:45.190
What happened to your crew?

408
00:25:46.570 --> 00:25:48.320
They'll be fine.

409
00:25:49.900 --> 00:25:53.490
What about your own ship and crew?

410
00:25:55.330 --> 00:25:57.080
I came here alone.

411
00:25:58.040 --> 00:26:01.540
That metal monster ate my ship.

412
00:26:01.540 --> 00:26:03.500
Screw that thing!

413
00:26:03.500 --> 00:26:05.750
That's terrible...

414
00:26:06.130 --> 00:26:07.000
Yeah!

415
00:26:07.000 --> 00:26:09.460
And I'm getting hungry now...

416
00:26:11.470 --> 00:26:13.840
Oh yeah, me too!

417
00:26:13.840 --> 00:26:15.850
Let's find a restaurant.

418
00:26:15.850 --> 00:26:17.350
I'm hungry, too!

419
00:26:17.350 --> 00:26:19.560
But, Luffy, do you have any money?

420
00:26:20.520 --> 00:26:22.600
Hey, boneheads!

421
00:26:22.600 --> 00:26:24.150
There's no restaurant here!

422
00:26:26.980 --> 00:26:28.940
This place belongs to the government.

423
00:26:31.400 --> 00:26:32.740
I'll fill you in.

424
00:26:33.740 --> 00:26:36.700
This island is called Egghead!

425
00:26:37.200 --> 00:26:39.620
It's said to be 500 years in the future.

426
00:26:39.620 --> 00:26:42.710
It's the island that houses Dr. Vegapunk's lab!

427
00:26:44.210 --> 00:26:45.750
Vegapunk!

428
00:26:45.750 --> 00:26:47.170
I know that name!

429
00:26:50.420 --> 00:26:52.260
I have business...

430
00:26:53.050 --> 00:26:54.880
with that quack!

431
00:27:10.360 --> 00:27:12.280
Everyone! Are you all right?!

432
00:27:15.410 --> 00:27:18.620
Is the Sunny all right?

433
00:27:27.290 --> 00:27:29.540
A... A...

434
00:27:29.540 --> 00:27:32.590
– A giant robot!
– A giant robot!

435
00:27:32.960 --> 00:27:34.550
Who could possibly...?

436
00:27:47.730 --> 00:27:49.310
Someone's coming out!

437
00:27:50.270 --> 00:27:52.150
This won't do...

438
00:27:53.030 --> 00:27:54.940
Yet another failure.

439
00:27:57.030 --> 00:28:00.370
Why can't I suppress
the urges of living beings?!

440
00:28:02.290 --> 00:28:03.790
I'm at my wit's end!

441
00:28:03.790 --> 00:28:07.670
I don't know who you are, but thank you!

442
00:28:07.670 --> 00:28:09.000
You saved us!

443
00:28:09.000 --> 00:28:13.250
The Mecha-Shark's only orders...

444
00:28:18.470 --> 00:28:21.680
were to scout, report, and bombard.

445
00:28:22.060 --> 00:28:25.350
But if it eats their ships,
there won't be any valuables left.

446
00:28:26.020 --> 00:28:28.350
It must be a programming error.

447
00:28:36.530 --> 00:28:37.650
Now...

448
00:28:37.650 --> 00:28:40.990
Who said anything about
rescuing you pirates?!

449
00:28:40.990 --> 00:28:45.660
I'm just a plain old genius scientist
working for the World Government!

450
00:28:49.500 --> 00:28:52.000
I'm Dr. Vegapunk!

451
00:28:54.050 --> 00:28:57.800
– What?!
– What?!

452
00:29:00.500 --> 00:29:05.590
Running so long, lost track of just how long it’s been

453
00:29:06.440 --> 00:29:12.950
Collected scars while striving, not even trying, beneath my skin

454
00:29:13.450 --> 00:29:20.370
But in the back of my head the dream is not dead, I remember a map

455
00:29:20.450 --> 00:29:26.660
to a treasure still gleaming, it’s within our grasp

456
00:29:26.800 --> 00:29:33.570
Can you feel my heart? Feelings I impart

457
00:29:33.530 --> 00:29:40.680
The promises are there; they're deep down but still primed to share

458
00:29:40.810 --> 00:29:49.790
Peerless dreams kept close, the dreams that always matter most

459
00:29:49.970 --> 00:29:55.550
Before we set sail why not raise a toast?

460
00:29:55.660 --> 00:30:02.570
So I pen this note to you! Dear sunrise, I’ll see you soon

461
00:30:02.730 --> 00:30:09.760
See the smile I saw the day that I sang this song to you

462
00:30:09.740 --> 00:30:16.810
And regardless of our age, these mem’ries will still remain

463
00:30:16.710 --> 00:30:23.920
Won’t forget until this wish makes it to you
